sections.english:
Indeed, bhikkhus, whatever recluses or brahmins do not understand the eye faculty, do not understand the origin of the eye faculty, do not understand the cessation of the eye faculty, and do not understand the path leading to the cessation of the eye faculty;
who do not understand the ear faculty, do not understand the origin of the ear faculty, do not understand the cessation of the ear faculty, and do not understand the path leading to the cessation of the ear faculty;
who do not understand the nose faculty, do not understand the origin of the nose faculty, do not understand the cessation of the nose faculty, and do not understand the path leading to the cessation of the nose faculty;
who do not understand the tongue faculty, do not understand the origin of the tongue faculty, do not understand the cessation of the tongue faculty, and do not understand the path leading to the cessation of the tongue faculty;
who do not understand the body faculty, do not understand the origin of the body faculty, do not understand the cessation of the body faculty, and do not understand the path leading to the cessation of the body faculty;
who do not understand the mind faculty, do not understand the origin of the mind faculty, do not understand the cessation of the mind faculty, and do not understand the path leading to the cessation of the mind faculty—
Such venerable ones, bhikkhus, are not regarded by me as recluses among recluses, nor as brahmins among brahmins; nor do they, having directly known and realized for themselves in this very life, attain and dwell in the goal of recluseship and the goal of brahminhood.

But whatever recluses or brahmins, bhikkhus, understand the eye faculty, understand the origin of the eye faculty, understand the cessation of the eye faculty, and understand the path leading to the cessation of the eye faculty;
who understand the ear faculty, understand the origin of the ear faculty, understand the cessation of the ear faculty, and understand the path leading to the cessation of the ear faculty;
who understand the nose faculty, understand the origin of the nose faculty, understand the cessation of the nose faculty, and understand the path leading to the cessation of the nose faculty;
who understand the tongue faculty, understand the origin of the tongue faculty, understand the cessation of the tongue faculty, and understand the path leading to the cessation of the tongue faculty;
who understand the body faculty, understand the origin of the body faculty, understand the cessation of the body faculty, and understand the path leading to the cessation of the body faculty;
who understand the mind faculty, understand the origin of the mind faculty, understand the cessation of the mind faculty, and understand the path leading to the cessation of the mind faculty—
Such venerable ones, bhikkhus, are regarded by me as recluses among recluses, and as brahmins among brahmins; and they, having directly known and realized for themselves in this very life, attain and dwell in the goal of recluseship and the goal of brahminhood.

The Tenth. The Chapter on the Six Faculties is the third. Its summary: Renewed existence, Understanding life, One-seeder, Pure, Stream-enterer, Arahant, Fully Enlightened One, and the two Recluses and Brahmins.
